Notes:

This jupyter notebook is for EDA (Exploratory Data Analysis). The code is written by readability and undestandability over everything method. This means the notebook usually contains duplicated code segments cell by cell. This is the result of conscious decisions. The code may run slower and use more resource, but this coding style helps people to understand the logic of EDA more easily. Fancy, pythonic one-liners can be good for eyes, but we know, in data science people have really different background. Some of them has hard programming skills, some one them isn't. If you want to know, how a fancy code looks like, check one of the attached python files.

This phase contains opening the dataset and making a fast integrity check. It means printing the dataset and check the name of columns and the type of values.

Dropping unnecessary columns¶

Drop all columns that contain only NaN values.

In [5]:
data.dropna(axis=1, inplace=True)
columns = list(data.columns)

For a good EDA, that focuses on to describe the diseases, there is no need to handle all columns. They can be removed to work faster and smoothly. The following columns are marked for removing:

  • Follow-up #
  • OriginalImage[Width
  • Height]
  • OriginalImagePixelSpacing[x
  • y]

all_ages = Counter()

for age in data['Patient Age'].iteritems():
    if age[1] <= 10:
        all_ages[10] += 1
    elif age[1] <= 20:
        all_ages[20] += 1
    elif age[1] <= 30:
        all_ages[30] += 1
    elif age[1] <= 40:
        all_ages[40] += 1
    elif age[1] <= 50:
        all_ages[50] += 1
    elif age[1] <= 60:
        all_ages[60] += 1
    elif age[1] <= 70:
        all_ages[70] += 1
    elif age[1] <= 80:
        all_ages[80] += 1
    elif age[1] <= 90:
        all_ages[90] += 1
    elif age[1] <= 100:

Remove young and old patients' data¶

An adult body is different than a young one. That's why it is advised to remove all the data that are related to young patients. In this case young means a person under 21 years. There are only 35 patient above 91 years. It is a really small number, so it does not add enough information to the model, but it makes the learning noisy.

In [14]:
data = data[(data['Patient Age'] >= 21) & (data['Patient Age'] < 90)]
In [15]:
# Create the `diseases` and `diseasesonly` variables for future use
diseases = []
disease_counter = Counter()

for value in set(data['Finding Labels'].unique()):
    labels = value.split('|')
    for label in labels:
        disease_counter[label] += 1

diseases = sorted(disease_counter)

diseasesonly = diseases[:]
diseasesonly.remove('No Finding')

Check the co-morbidity between different diseases¶

In [16]:
co_morbidity = {}

for disease in diseases:
    co_morbidity[disease] = Counter()

for disease in diseases:
    for elem in list(data['Finding Labels']):
        labels = elem.split('|')
        if disease in labels:
            if len(labels) == 1:
                if labels[0] == disease:
                    co_morbidity[disease][disease] += 1
                else:
                    continue
            else:
                for label in labels:
                    if label == disease:
                        continue
                    else:
                        co_morbidity[disease][label] += 1

for disease in diseases:
    disease_sum = sum(co_morbidity[disease].values())
    text = '\nCo-diseases with {}'.format(disease)
    limiter = ''
    for i in range(len(text)-1):
        limiter += '-'
    print('\nCo-diseases with {}'.format(disease))
    print(limiter)
    for i in diseases:
        if disease_sum != 0:
            ratio = co_morbidity[disease][i] / disease_sum * 100
        else:
            ratio = 0.0
        print('{:>18}: {:6} ({:6.2f}%)'.format(i, co_morbidity[disease][i], ratio))

    if disease != 'No Finding':
        other_diseases_name = sorted(co_morbidity[disease].keys())
        other_diseases_name.remove(disease)
        other_diseases_count = []
        for other_disease in other_diseases_name:
            other_diseases_count.append(co_morbidity[disease][other_disease])

        x_pos = [ii for ii, _ in enumerate(other_diseases_name)]

        plt.bar(x_pos, other_diseases_count, color='green')
        plt.xlabel('Diseases').set_fontsize(14)
        plt.ylabel('Frequency').set_fontsize(14)
        plt.title('Distribution of how frequently {} occurs relative to other diseases\n'.format(disease)).set_fontsize(14)
        plt.xticks(x_pos, other_diseases_name, rotation=45, ha='right',
             rotation_mode='anchor')
        plt.show()

Visualize co-morbidites with heatmaps¶

Heatmap for normal values¶

In [17]:
# The hreshold is used for making nicer output.
threshold = 2000

heatmap = np.zeros([15, 15], dtype=np.uint32)

for idy, disease in enumerate(diseases):
    for idx, i in enumerate(diseases):
        heatmap[idx][idy] = co_morbidity[disease][i]

len_diseases = len(diseases)

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15,15))
im = ax.imshow(heatmap, vmax=threshold)

def show_x_ray(img, img_data, label):

    f = plt.figure()
    f.set_figwidth(20)

    p1 = f.add_subplot(1, 2, 1)
    p1.set_title('Sample X-ray: {}'.format(label),fontsize=16)
    plt.imshow(img, cmap='gray')
    
    p2 = f.add_subplot(1, 2, 2)
    p2.set_title('Histogram: Intensity Distribution\n Average of {} disease without co-morbidities'.format(label),fontsize=16)
    p2.axes.set_xlim(xmin= 0, xmax=255)
    plt.hist(img_data.ravel(), bins = 256)

    plt.show()
    
    # Order statistics
    data_min = np.amin(img_data)
    data_max = np.amax(img_data)
    data_percentiles = []
    for i in range(0,101,10):
        data_percentiles.append((i, np.percentile(img_data, i)))
    text_percentile = ''
    for i in data_percentiles:
        text_percentile += '{}'.format(i[1])
        if i[0] != 100:
            text_percentile += ' - '
    
    # Averages and variances
    data_median = np.median(img_data)
    data_mean = np.mean(img_data)
    data_avg = np.average(img_data)
    data_std = np.std(img_data)
    
    print('Statistics')
    print('min: {:3} | max: {:3} | median: {:6.2f} | mean: {:6.2f} | avg: {:6.2f} | std: {:6.2f}'.format(data_min, data_max, data_median, data_mean, data_avg, data_std))
    print('percentiles: {}'.format(text_percentile))

co_morbidity = {}

for disease in diseases:
    co_morbidity[disease] = Counter()

for disease in diseases:
    for elem in list(data['Finding Labels']):
        labels = elem.split('|')
        if disease in labels:
            if len(labels) == 1:
                if labels[0] == disease:
                    co_morbidity[disease][disease] += 1
                else:
                    continue
            else:
                for label in labels:
                    if label == disease:
                        continue
                    else:
                        co_morbidity[disease][label] += 1

for disease in diseases:
    disease_sum = sum(co_morbidity[disease].values())
    text = '\nCo-diseases with {}'.format(disease)
    limiter = ''
    for i in range(len(text)-1):
        limiter += '-'
    print('\nCo-diseases with {}'.format(disease))
    print(limiter)
    for i in diseases:
        if disease_sum != 0:
            ratio = co_morbidity[disease][i] / disease_sum * 100
        else:
            ratio = 0.0
        print('{:>18}: {:6} ({:6.2f}%)'.format(i, co_morbidity[disease][i], ratio))

    if disease != 'No Finding':
        other_diseases_name = sorted(co_morbidity[disease].keys())
        other_diseases_name.remove(disease)
        other_diseases_count = []
        for other_disease in other_diseases_name:
            other_diseases_count.append(co_morbidity[disease][other_disease])

        x_pos = [ii for ii, _ in enumerate(other_diseases_name)]

        plt.bar(x_pos, other_diseases_count, color='green')
        plt.xlabel('Diseases').set_fontsize(14)
        plt.ylabel('Frequency').set_fontsize(14)
        plt.title('Distribution of how frequently {} occurs relative to other diseases\n'.format(disease)).set_fontsize(14)
        plt.xticks(x_pos, other_diseases_name, rotation=45, ha='right',
             rotation_mode='anchor')
        plt.show()

Create train, test and valid subsets¶

In [28]:
save_data = False

for disease in diseasesonly:
    
    data['target'] = data['is{}'.format(disease)].apply(lambda x: 'Y' if x == 1.0 else 'N')

    train_valid_df, test_df = skl.train_test_split(data, test_size=0.2, stratify=data['target'])

    train_df, valid_df = skl.train_test_split(train_valid_df, test_size=0.1,
                                              stratify=train_valid_df['target'])

    # Balance the ratio of positive and non-positive to 50:50 since it is refers to the real life scenario.
    p_train = train_df[train_df['target'] == 'Y'].index.tolist()
    np_train = train_df[train_df['target'] == 'N'].index.tolist()
    np_sample = sample(np_train, len(p_train))
    train_df = train_df.loc[p_train + np_sample]
    train_ratio = len(train_df[train_df['target'] == 'Y']) / len(train_df)
    train_df['target'] = train_df['target'].apply(lambda x: '1' if x == 'Y' else '0')

    # Balance the ratio of positive and non-positive to 20:80 since it is refers to the real life scenario.
    p_valid = test_df[test_df['target'] == 'Y'].index.tolist()
    np_valid =  test_df[test_df['target'] == 'N'].index.tolist()
    np_sample = sample(np_valid, 4 * len(p_valid))
    test_df = test_df.loc[p_valid + np_sample]
    test_ratio =  len(test_df[test_df['target'] == 'Y']) / len(test_df)
    test_df['target'] = test_df['target'].apply(lambda x: '1' if x == 'Y' else '0')

    # Balance the ratio of positive and non-positive to 20:80 since it is refers to the real life scenario.
    p_valid = valid_df[valid_df['target'] == 'Y'].index.tolist()
    np_valid =  valid_df[valid_df['target'] == 'N'].index.tolist()
    np_sample = sample(np_valid, 4 * len(p_valid))
    valid_df = valid_df.loc[p_valid + np_sample]
    valid_ratio =  len(valid_df[valid_df['target'] == 'Y']) / len(valid_df)
    valid_df['target'] = valid_df['target'].apply(lambda x: '1' if x == 'Y' else '0')

    print('\n{}'.format(disease))
    text =''
    for i in range(len(disease)):
        text += '-'
    print(text)
    print('Total length of train dataframe: {}'.format(len(train_df)))
    print('Total length of test dataframe:  {}'.format(len(test_df)))
    print('Total length of valid dataframe: {}'.format(len(valid_df)))
    print('Number of `positive` cases in train dataframe:     {}'.format(
                                                                  len(train_df[train_df['target'] == '1'])))
    print('Number of `non-positive` cases in train dataframe: {}'.format(
                                                                  len(train_df[train_df['target'] == '0'])))
    print('Number of `positive` cases in test  dataframe:     {}'.format(
                                                                  len(test_df[test_df['target'] == '1'])))
    print('Number of `non-positive` cases in test dataframe:  {}'.format(
                                                                  len(test_df[test_df['target'] == '0'])))
    print('Number of `positive` cases in valid dataframe:     {}'.format(
                                                                  len(valid_df[valid_df['target'] == '1'])))
    print('Number of `non-positive` cases in valid dataframe: {}'.format(
                                                                  len(valid_df[valid_df['target'] == '0'])))
    print('Balanced ratio of `positive` and `non-positive` in train dataframe: {}'
          .format(train_ratio))
    print('Balanced ratio of `positive` and `non-positive` in test dataframe:  {}'
          .format(test_ratio))
    print('Balanced ratio of `positive` and `non-positive` in valid dataframe: {}'
          .format(valid_ratio))    
    print(' *Values above refers to the `positive` cases only.') 

    if save_data is True:
        train_df.drop(train_df.columns.difference(['Image Index', 'target', 'Patient ID', 'Finding Labels']), 1, inplace=True)
        train_df.to_csv('./csv/train-{}.csv'.format(disease), sep='\t', index=False)
        test_df.drop(test_df.columns.difference(['Image Index','target', 'Patient ID', 'Finding Labels']), 1, inplace=True)
        test_df.to_csv('./csv/test-{}.csv'.format(disease), sep='\t', index=False)
        valid_df.drop(valid_df.columns.difference(['Image Index','target', 'Patient ID', 'Finding Labels']), 1, inplace=True)
        valid_df.to_csv('./csv/valid-{}.csv'.format(disease), sep='\t', index=False)

Dataset by the different diseases¶

In [36]:
all_labels = []

for disease in diseases:
    for elem in list(data['Finding Labels']):
        labels = elem.split('|')
        if disease in labels:
            if len(labels) == 1:
                if labels[0] == disease:
                    all_labels.append(labels[0])
                else:
                    continue
            else:
                for label in labels:
                    if label == disease:
                        continue
                    else:
                        all_labels.append(label)

all_labels = Counter(all_labels)
